{"by":"m6z","id":47773846,"parent":47773594,"text":"How to quantify which font is &quot;best&quot; is a tricky question.  I do flip through available programming fonts on occasion just to see if something feels right.  A recent favorite is Monaspace Neon from Lettermatic.  One detail actually is that I find I like zeros that are noticeably different than an uppercase letter &#x27;O&#x27;.  In Monospace Neon for example the zero has a dot in the middle.","time":1776219007,"type":"comment"}